<%= react_component("RailsFormExample", prerender: false, trace: true, id: "RailsFormExample-react-component-0") %>

<hr/>
<h2>useRailsForm 422 round trip</h2>
<p>
  This form is built with the <code>useRailsForm</code> hook
  (<code>react-on-rails/useRailsForm</code>) and posts JSON to
  <code>ContactMessagesController#create</code>, a plain Rails action that uses
  the opt-in <code>ReactOnRails::Controller::FormResponders</code> concern.
</p>
<ol>
  <li>Submit the empty form: the controller responds 422 with
    <code>{ errors: { field: ["message"] } }</code> and each field renders its
    errors.</li>
  <li>Fill in valid values (a real email, a message of 10+ characters) and the
    submit succeeds.</li>
</ol>
